column1:
The last words uttered by the last white man before his last breath, circa 2031;
Somewhere in North America;

"Well, at least I did everything I could legally. At least I adhered to the law and to the basic rights of others. At least I will be known as the white man with good optics. That will show them-" 

This is my clear message to you people; I hope the meaning translates well.
